SIMPLE: expeditate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expeditate
<hw>Ex*ped"i*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>expeditatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>expeditare</ets> to expeditate;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>, foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Eng. Forest Laws)</fld> <def>To deprive of the claws or the balls
of the fore feet; <as>as, to <ex>expeditate</ex> a dog that he may not
chase deer</as>. See also <er>declaw</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expedite</ent>⟦br⟧
